  29:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   @verbatim
  30:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****  ===============================================================================
  31:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****                           ##### RTC Operating Condition #####
  32:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****  ===============================================================================
  33:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The real-time clock (RTC) and the RTC backup registers can be powered
  34:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        from the VBAT voltage when the main VDD supply is powered off.
  35:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        To retain the content of the RTC backup registers and supply the RTC
  36:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        when VDD is turned off, VBAT pin can be connected to an optional
  37:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        standby voltage supplied by a battery or by another source.
  38:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  39:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****                    ##### Backup Domain Reset #####
  40:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****  ===============================================================================
  41:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The backup domain reset sets all RTC registers and the RCC_BDCR register
  42:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        to their reset values.
  43:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        A backup domain reset is generated when one of the following events occurs:
  44:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) Software reset, triggered by setting the BDRST bit in the
  45:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****         RCC Backup domain control register (RCC_BDCR).
  46:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) VDD or VBAT power on, if both supplies have previously been powered off.
  47:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) Tamper detection event resets all data backup registers.
  48:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  49:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****                    ##### Backup Domain Access #####
  50:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==================================================================
  51:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] After reset, the backup domain (RTC registers and RTC backup data registers)
  52:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        is protected against possible unwanted write accesses.
  53:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] To enable access to the RTC Domain and RTC registers, proceed as follows:
  54:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable access to RTC domain using the HAL_PWR_EnableBkUpAccess() function.
  55:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Call the function HAL_RCCEx_PeriphCLKConfig with RCC_PERIPHCLK_RTC for
  56:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****         PeriphClockSelection and select RTCClockSelection (LSE, LSI or HSEdiv32)
  57:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable RTC Clock using the __HAL_RCC_RTC_ENABLE() function.
  58:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  59:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****                   ##### How to use RTC Driver #####
  60:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****  ===================================================================
  61:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
  62:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable the RTC domain access (see description in the section above).
  63:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Configure the RTC Prescaler (Asynchronous and Synchronous) and RTC hour
  64:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****         format using the HAL_RTC_Init() function.
  65:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  66:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *** Time and Date configuration ***
  67:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ===================================
  68:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
  69:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Calendar (Time and Date) use the HAL_RTC_SetTime()
  70:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****         and HAL_RTC_SetDate() functions.
  71:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To read the RTC Calendar, use the HAL_RTC_GetTime() and HAL_RTC_GetDate() functions.
  72:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  73:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *** Alarm configuration ***
  74:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ===========================
  75:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
  76:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Alarm use the HAL_RTC_SetAlarm() function.
  77:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****             You can also configure the RTC Alarm with interrupt mode using the
  78:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****             HAL_RTC_SetAlarm_IT() function.
  79:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To read the RTC Alarm, use the HAL_RTC_GetAlarm() function.
  80:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  81:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****                   ##### RTC and low power modes #####
  82:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==================================================================
  83:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The MCU can be woken up from a low power mode by an RTC alternate
  84:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        function.
  85:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The RTC alternate functions are the RTC alarms (Alarm A and Alarm B),
ARM GAS  C:\Users\DELL\AppData\Local\Temp\cc4T5Hun.s 			page 3


  86:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        RTC wakeup, RTC tamper event detection and RTC time stamp event detection.
  87:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        These RTC alternate functions can wake up the system from the Stop and
  88:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        Standby low power modes.
  89:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The system can also wake up from low power modes without depending
  90:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        on an external interrupt (Auto-wakeup mode), by using the RTC alarm
  91:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        or the RTC wakeup events.
  92:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The RTC provides a programmable time base for waking up from the
  93:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        Stop or Standby mode at regular intervals.
  94:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        Wakeup from STOP and STANDBY modes is possible only when the RTC clock source
  95:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****        is LSE or LSI.
  96:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  97:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *** Callback registration ***
  98:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   =============================================
  99:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   When The compilation define USE_HAL_RTC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 100:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all callbacks
 101:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   are set to the corresponding weak functions. This is the recommended configuration
 102:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   in order to optimize memory/code consumption footprint/performances.
 103:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 104:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   The compilation define USE_RTC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 105:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 106:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Use Function HAL_RTC_RegisterCallback() to register an interrupt callback.
 107:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 108:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Function HAL_RTC_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 109:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmAEventCallback             : RTC Alarm A Event callback.
 110:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmBEventCallback             : RTC Alarm B Event callback.
 111:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) TimeStampEventCallback          : RTC TimeStamp Event callback.
 112:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) WakeUpTimerEventCallback        : RTC WakeUpTimer Event callback.
 113:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) SSRUEventCallback               : RTC SSRU Event callback.
 114:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper1EventCallback            : RTC Tamper 1 Event callback.
 115:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper2EventCallback            : RTC Tamper 2 Event callback.
