 173:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 174:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   By default, after the HAL_RTC_Init() and when the state is HAL_RTC_STATE_RESET,
 175:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions :
 176:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   examples AlarmAEventCallback(), TimeStampEventCallback().
 177:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit callbacks that are reset to the legacy weak function
 178:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   in the HAL_RTC_Init()/HAL_RTC_DeInit() only when these callbacks are null
 179:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   (not registered beforehand).
 180:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, HAL_RTC_Init()/HAL_RTC_DeInit()
 181:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 182:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 183:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_RTC_STATE_READY state only.
 184:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 185:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   in HAL_RTC_STATE_READY or HAL_RTC_STATE_RESET state,
 186:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 187:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 188:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   using HAL_RTC_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_RTC_DeInit()
 189:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   or HAL_RTC_Init() function.
 190:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 191:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   When The compilation define USE_HAL_RTC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 192:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all callbacks
 193:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   are set to the corresponding weak functions.
 194:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 195:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   @endverbatim
 196:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   */
