2101:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c **** /**
2102:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @brief  Wait until the RTC Time and Date registers (RTC_TR and RTC_DR) are
2103:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         synchronized with RTC APB clock.
2104:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @note   The RTC Resynchronization mode is write protected, use the
2105:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         __HAL_RTC_WRITEPROTECTION_DISABLE() before calling this function.
2106:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @note   To read the calendar through the shadow registers after Calendar
ARM GAS  C:\Users\DELL\AppData\Local\Temp\cc4T5Hun.s 			page 47


2107:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         initialization, calendar update or after wakeup from low power modes
2108:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         the software must first clear the RSF flag.
2109:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         The software must then wait until it is set again before reading
2110:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         the calendar, which means that the calendar registers have been
2111:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         correctly copied into the RTC_TR and RTC_DR shadow registers.
2112:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @param  hrtc RTC handle
2113:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @retval HAL status
